It has a starting point.
The sentences logically follow one another.
The ending connects to the beginning.
The past tense and sentence structure conveys time has occured/passed.

There is a beginning and middle--and the desire for a yet unfulfilled end.
There is a "character" need and inciting incident as well as background.
There are problems along the way, and a central problem.
There are chatracters outside of them eg. the mechanics.

goal:::text_box: educate people on bodybuilding.

The author tells us how he began bodybuilding.

Then he tells a story about working out with his friend who is shorter, and how that made it easier for his friend than for himself.

goal:::text_box: The author of this text wants to make people happy.

The author tells us of one of his favorite songs.

They then tell us they watch a show based on the song title.

Then they tell us how it made then smile.

goal:::text_box: to ask for advice about an unsatisfactory car he bought
story_decision_explanation:::text_box: The author tells us about his purchase of the car and the problems with it. He says the dealership won't fix it or honor the warranty.

goal:::text_box: complain about a video game design
